				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tradeskills... which ones for bards?<a name="47976"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 24 04 8:08 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Baking.
<br />

<br />
w/o a doubt in my opinion.
<br />

<br />
Everyone suggests brewing as the cheapest to get to 248, that is true, however the price will kill you when attempting the trophy.  In addition to the 4-8k you'll spend getting the seal, you have to buy a corking device (which you have no chance of making).  That can set you back 1-5k depending.
<br />

<br />
Baking trophy uses a dairy spoon, that's a very low triv for smithing I believe, and dirt cheap, and found on vendors for 1pp as ppl use them to skill up.
<br />

<br />
Baking can be done storebought to 192, and then after that you have the option of :-
<br />

<br />
a) Improving fishing in PoStorms for Storm Salmon (triv 215).
<br />

<br />
b) Planar fruit pies (good stat food, regardless of it's 30pp each sale price) - you will need celestial essence, but a few swarm kites in ME will get you as much of that as you need if you carry a mixing bowl around with you and the celestial solvents.
<br />

<br />
c) Misty Thicket Picnics - keep veggies, fruit, and kill brownies in lfay.
<br />

<br />
Now, people will have their own opinions about the easiest skill to get up, I now have 250 baking raw, and 100+ in the rest (170+ if you don't count tailoring), and baking has been the easiest to get components for.
<br />

<br />
You should attempt the trophy @ 240 raw skill +5% geerlok == 252 effective.
<br />
</span></td>
