				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tradeskills... which ones for bards?<a name="51587"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 13 04 3:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One consideration is our self buffs. We can buff strength and thus make the high-end of Blacksmithing less intolerable than it might otherwise be (higher skill-up rate). (the shift from 130 to 250 strength doubles the skill-up rate).
<br />

<br />
This is not to say that as a bard I get something good out of smithing, but rather, if I want to smith, I have an advantage being a bard.
<br />

<br />
eqtrader.com has a major section on quests with a tradeskill component to them. That might help give you ideas of what you want to do.
<br />

<br />
Bards also have the benefit of foraging, which gets you a lot of tradeskill supplies that you might otherwise need to buy from foragers. This is particularly useful for Baking and Brewing, which use a lot of foraged items. Also, LDoN armor actually turns a nice profit if you forage the temper ingredients during adventures. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Finally, tradeskills are best thought of as fun first and maybe, if you are lucky, profitable in the very long run.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
