				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tradeskills... which ones for bards?<a name="51611"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 13 04 10:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>By that same token, since you may as well do fletching, and you can forage...
<br />

<br />
You may as well use Elegy? + VoTS + Epic + MGB KEI and do baking (or brewing)
<br />

<br />
If you're not a 1750 tradeskill freak, and you only want the trophy then my own anecdotal forum trawling experience reveals that most people on eqtraders that have attempted the trophy appear to have succeeded 1 in 2 sometimes as bad as 1 in 5.  So final cost of the trophy is probably (5k + x) *2.  5k is pretty much what you will pay for all the individual components to the Artisan's Seal, x being the price of the tradeskill item.
<br />

<br />
If the only concern is making the trophy (cash doesn't appear to be an issue for the topic starter) then yes, brewing is the fastest.  2 or 3 types of combines, all store bought == 248 skill.  Corking devices are relatively expensive however.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
