			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tradeskills... which ones for bards?<a name="51656"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 13 04 12:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Overall brewing is probably the quickest, easiest, and cheapest to get over 200 and you can do it on 2-3 recipies.
<br />

<br />
Baking is a cakewalk up to 191 (fish rolls or fillets up to 134/143 then patty melts to 191).  With the new GoD recipies, getting up into the 200's isn't bad either.
<br />

<br />
Pottery is fairly easy.  It takes more combines, but getting to 199 is easily doable (bowls/casserole dishes).  
<br />

<br />
Fletching and Jeweling are both simple if not more expensive.  Jewel crafting isn't too painful if you have an enchanter that will enchant stack after stack after stack of metals.  Get the geerlock and stay within 10-15 points of your trivial.  You'll break even on successful combines with enchanted metals.  Fletching is just a matter of finding a cheap path and eating the cost.
<br />

<br />
Smithing isn't bad up to 115, it gets expensive or very time consuming with farming after that.
<br />

<br />
Tailoring is just painful anyway you look at it.
<br />

<br />
Fishing is quasi-tradeskillish and just takes time.  Its relatively cheap.  
<br />

<br />
Begging is also quasi-tradeskillish and is boring and takes a ton of time.
<br />

<br />
Bard forage caps at 55.  I've found this allows me to use it when I need, but getting the quantities needed for skillups is a royal pain.
<br />

<br />
Also, you can get to 54 in any tradeskill for FREE in Abysmal Sea doing the quests.  The only skill I had under 55 was tailoring when this came out, but it sure beat farming for the items for those levels.
<br />

<br />
I downloaded a spreadsheet someone did showing the progressions they used/recommend for every tradeskill.  I haven't asked for permission yet to post it on my website, but if anyone is interested in it, email me at jarroll@xegonybard.com and I'll forward it to you.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=402012">Jarroll</a>, Bard of Xegony</p>
<img src="http://www.the-commune.com/modules/PNphpBB2/images/avatars/gallery/kia/anielg.gif"></span></td>
