			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tradeskills... which ones for bards?<a name="51871"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 14 04 12:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This list may vary but speaking from personal experience I find it dead on. 
<br />

<br />
From Easiest to most difficult:
<br />

<br />
Brewing
<br />
Jewelcraft
<br />
Baking
<br />
Fletching
<br />
Pottery
<br />
Tailoring
<br />
Smithing
<br />

<br />
Brewing - so easy. 0 - 250 in less than 4k pf plat and all but the last 2 points 249/250 can be done on a vendor.
<br />

<br />
Jewelcrafting -  14k to get 200 - 250. If you have decent faction with Thurg you can do all your jewelcrafting right at the Jewelry vendors. I enchanted no metals and sold back my success to the vendors. 
<br />

<br />
Baking - Realatively easy if you camp the bazaar or exp in BOT. 
<br />

<br />
Fletching - While a lil more on the expensive side, you can do bows all the way to 250 or camp the bazaar for Acrylia and Condensed Shadow for arrows after you get to 202 from vendor sold arrow combines.
<br />

<br />
Pottery - 40k for 200 - 250 and unless you have a pocket Enchanter, your at the mercy of the Bazaar for your encahnted needs. 
<br />

<br />
Tailoring - Very difficult. I spent a lot of time having to farm Wyvern Hides in Cobalt scar and fishing up the Cod as well. Cost was through the roof to go just from 200 - 250.
<br />

<br />
Smithing - Amazingly expensive and diffuclt if your half elf with no cultural. With no cultural your stuck with pretty much only two routes to get to 250. 
<br />

<br />
Now in terms of profit made, Pottery, Baking, Tailoring have been my money makers. Pop idols, Hero sandwiches and Pop tailored items have made my bank account swell as of late. I am still in the red with money spent getting all trades to 250 but I am slowly starting to come out on top. And with smithing at 231 and rising quickly, I will be done with skilling up forever and then I can stack my plat to share with my friends lol.
<br />

<br />
If you do decide to go for trades make sure you get your INT or WIS as high as possible or you will be spending more time hitting combine than necessary. Camp the bazaar and get you a secondary trade suit to max your int/wis. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
